      },
      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:31:18",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/31/639",
      "text": [
        "ْكَسَرَ اَلْعَمُودُ لَمْ يَنْفَعْ وَتِدٌ وَ لاَ طُنُبٌ وَ لاَ غِشَاءٌ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.639 - The Messenger of Allah (sw) said:\n\"The example of prayer is like the central pole of a tent. If the central pole is firmly established, then the ropes, pegs, and coverings remain firm; but if the central pole breaks, then neither the pegs, ropes, nor coverings are of any use.\""
        ]
      }
    },
